	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-193041">
	<article id="article-comment-193041">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Kaycee A.</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">February 01, 2026 at 9:15 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Simple, easy to put together &#8211; and delicious. I kind of wish it had a little more &#8220;bite&#8221; to complement the sweetness. I&#8217;ll have to try a few spices with some &#8220;heat&#8221; to see what I can create. Great recipe &#8211; juicy! Be careful not to overcook the meat. I only cooked one tenderloin &#8211; so for me 25 minutes was a few minutes too long. Still tasted wonderful &amp; tender, though. Had a wonderful &#8220;crust&#8221; to it, too &#8211; which was a great surprise!</p>
<p class="tasty-recipes-ratings"><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-outline" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="1"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-outline" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="2"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-outline" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="3"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-outline" data-tr-clip="100" data-rating="4"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span><span class="tasty-recipes-rating tasty-recipes-rating-outline" data-tr-clip="0" data-rating="5"><svg class="tasty-recipes-svg"><use href="#wpt-star-full"></use></svg></span></p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-193041" data-commentid="193041" data-postid="3104" data-belowelement="article-comment-193041" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kaycee A." aria-label="Reply to Kaycee A.">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->

